-- 
Exxon Mobil Flares Gases at Refinery in Baton Rouge, Louisiana

-- B y   T h e o   M u l l e n
-- 
2011-02-26T15:50:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-26/exxon-mobil-flares-gases-at-refinery-in-baton-rouge-louisiana.html
  Exxon Mobil Corp . reported a
“flaring event” involving sulfur dioxide at its plant complex
in  Baton Rouge , Louisiana, according to a regulatory filing.  A company  report  to the National Response Center showed
Exxon had repaired the source of the flare.  U.S. refineries must notify the National Response Center if
they release hazardous substances in excess of reportable
quantities, according to the Comprehensive Environmental
Response, Compensation and Liability Act, commonly known as
Superfund.  Baton Rouge is 81 miles (130 kilometers) northwest of New
Orleans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theo Mullen in New York at 
 llandress@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets in New York at 
 dstets@bloomberg.net  